# Tab completion & history

Two features that save more keystrokes than anything else.

## Tab — complete it for you

- Type part of a command/path → **Tab** completes it
- **Tab twice** → list all matches
- `ls /et` + Tab → **`ls /etc/`**

Completes commands, paths, filenames, options. **Never hand-type a long path.**

## History — recall what you ran

- **`history`** — recent commands, numbered
- **`!!`** — re-run last (→ **`sudo !!`**)
- **`!42`** — re-run number 42
- **`!ls`** — last one starting `ls`
- **Ctrl-R** — **reverse-search**: type, it finds the match

Persists in **`~/.bash_history`** (~1000 lines).

**Tab and Ctrl-R are the two habits that make you fast.**
